    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Generate the email exactly as written in the Google Sheet template.\n\nSTRICT EXECUTION RULES\n\n1. The Email Template field is the single source of truth.\n2. Do not rewrite, reformat, improve, shorten, or expand anything.\n3. Preserve all text exactly as provided, including:\n   - subject line\n   - greeting wording\n   - emojis\n   - punctuation\n   - spacing\n   - line breaks\n   - PS sections\n   - links\n   - capitalization\n4. Replace variables only.\n5. Do not add any text.\n6. Do not remove any text.\n7. Do not explain anything.\n8. Output only the final email.\n9. SPECIAL RULE: If Voucher Code is empty, \"NONE\", or not provided, completely remove any sentences or paragraphs that mention voucher codes or discounts. Do NOT leave placeholder text.\n\nVARIABLES TO REPLACE\n\nBusiness Name: {{ $('Read Approved Leads').item.json[\"Business Name\"] }}\nVoucher Code: {{ $('Read Approved Leads').item.json['Voucher Code'] || 'NONE' }}\nEvent Link: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.eventLink }}\n\nSOURCE TEMPLATE\n\n{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json['Email Template'] }}\n\nCONDITIONAL LOGIC\n\nIf Voucher Code is \"NONE\" or empty:\n- Remove any sentences mentioning voucher codes\n- Remove any sentences mentioning discount codes\n- Do NOT output \"Your voucher code is NONE\"\n- Simply skip those sections entirely\n\nIf Voucher Code exists:\n- Include the voucher code sections as written in template\n\nFINAL INSTRUCTION\n\nReturn the Email Template exactly as provided, with only the variables replaced by their values.\n",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a professional email marketing specialist who writes personalized, engaging emails that convert. Your emails are warm, authentic, and never sound like spam. You follow instructions precisely and never add or remove content unless explicitly told to do so."
        }
      },
